The paper deals with recommendation systems, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks for assigning personalized confidence weights suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The development of a new batch-based learning algorithm may also place the paper under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of implicit feedback and the focus on efficient model learning may suggest the paper belongs to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
